1 - dragonstone
49 - diamond
150 - ruby
300 - emerald
500 - sapphire
The chance is 2/3 of the gem being [cut].<!--The cited tweet states banknoted, but was later corrected to mean cut: https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1260477262769553414-->}}

''Each time a gem is successfully looted, there is a 2/3 chance of it being cut instead of uncut.''

====Pre-roll====
{{DropsTableHead}}
{{DropsLineSkill|name=Onyx|quantity=1|rarity=1/50000|smw=No|skill=Thieving}}
{{DropsTableBottom}}

If the roll for an onyx fails, you then roll for the remaining gem types.
Once you have rolled a gem you then roll again to decide if it's cut or uncut.

